{"name": "django-enumfields", "metadata": {"name": "django-enumfields", "version": "2.1.1", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Framework :: Django :: 2.2", "Framework :: Django :: 3.0", "Framework :: Django :: 3.1", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP"], "home_page": "https://github.com/hzdg/django-enumfields", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Real Python Enums for Django.", "upload_time": 1614062465}, "documentation": ["This package lets you use real Python ([PEP435]-style) enums with Django.\n\n```{image} https://travis-ci.org/hzdg/django-enumfields.svg?branch=master\n:target: https://travis-ci.org/hzdg/django-enumfields\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/django-enumfields.svg\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/django-enumfields\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/django-enumfields.svg\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/django-enumfields/\n```\n\n# Installation\n\n1. `pip install django-enumfields`\n\n# Included Tools\n\n## EnumField, EnumIntegerField\n\n```python\nfrom enumfields import EnumField\nfrom enum import Enum\n\nclass Color(Enum):\n    RED = 'r'\n    GREEN = 'g'\n    BLUE = 'b'\n\nclass MyModel(models.Model):\n\n    color = EnumField(Color, max_length=1)\n```\n\nElsewhere:\n\n```python\nm = MyModel.objects.filter(color=Color.RED)\n```\n\n`EnumIntegerField` works identically, but the underlying storage mechanism is\nan `IntegerField` instead of a `CharField`.\n\n### Usage in Forms\n\nCall the `formfield` method to use an `EnumField` directly in a `Form`.\n\n```python\nclass MyForm(forms.Form):\n\n    color = EnumField(Color, max_length=1).formfield()\n```\n\n## Enum\n\nNormally, you just use normal [PEP435]-style enums, however, django-enumfields\nalso includes its own version of Enum with a few extra bells and whistles.\nNamely, the smart definition of labels which are used, for example, in admin\ndropdowns. By default, it will create labels by title-casing your constant\nnames. You can provide custom labels with a nested \"Labels\" class.\n\n```python\nfrom enumfields import EnumField, Enum  # Our own Enum class\n\nclass Color(Enum):\n    RED = 'r'\n    GREEN = 'g'\n    BLUE = 'b'\n\n    class Labels:\n        RED = 'A custom label'\n\nclass MyModel(models.Model):\n    color = EnumField(Color, max_length=1)\n\nassert Color.GREEN.label == 'Green'\nassert Color.RED.label == 'A custom label'\n```\n\n## EnumFieldListFilter\n\n`enumfields.admin.EnumFieldListFilter` is provided to allow using enums in\n`list_filter`.\n\n```python\nfrom enumfields.admin import EnumFieldListFilter\n\nclass MyModelAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):\n    list_filter = [('color', EnumFieldListFilter)]\n```\n\n## Django Rest Framework integration\n\n`EnumSupportSerializerMixin` mixin allows you to use enums in DRF serializers.\n\n```python\n# models.py\nfrom enumfields import EnumField\nfrom enum import Enum\n\nclass Color(Enum):\n    RED = 'r'\n    GREEN = 'g'\n    BLUE = 'b'\n\nclass MyModel(models.Model):\n    color = EnumField(Color, max_length=1)\n\n\n# serializers.py\nfrom enumfields.drf.serializers import EnumSupportSerializerMixin\nfrom rest_framework import serializers\nfrom .models import MyModel\n\nclass MyModelSerializer(EnumSupportSerializerMixin, serializers.ModelSerializer):\n    class Meta:\n        model = MyModel\n        fields = '__all__'\n```\n\n[pep435]: http://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0435/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "enumfields.drf.serializers", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "enumfields.drf.serializers.EnumSupportSerializerMixin", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "enumfields.drf.serializers.EnumSupportSerializerMixin.build_standard_field", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "field_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model_field", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "enumfields.drf.serializers.EnumSupportSerializerMixin.enumfield_options", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "enumfields.drf.serializers.EnumSupportSerializerMixin.enumfield_classes_to_replace", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "enumfields.drf.fields", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "enumfields.drf.fields.EnumField", "bases": ["ChoiceField"], "methods": [{"name": "enumfields.drf.fields.EnumField.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "enum", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lenient", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ints_as_names", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["---\nparam enum: The enumeration class.\nparam ints_as_names: Whether to serialize integer-valued enums by their name, not\n  the integer value\nparam lenient: Whether to allow lenient parsing (case-insensitive, by value or name)\ntype ints_as_names: bool\ntype lenient: bool\n---\n"]}, {"name": "enumfields.drf.fields.EnumField.to_representation", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "enumfields.drf.fields.EnumField.to_internal_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}